
MTK CCCI MD INIT Daemon is a service that used to control modem bootup and state change.
WHAT IT DOES?
=============
ccci_mdinit comunicates with ccci drvier to control modem life-cycle and state, such as  when to start and stop modem, 
how to handle flight mode, how to modem exception, and etc.

HOW IT WAS BUILT?
==================
It needs the following library:    
from AOSP
1.  libc.so
2.  libcutils.so
3.  libdl.so
4.  liblog.so
5.  libhardware_legacy.so
from MTK
1.  libnvram.so
2.  libccci_util.so

All source/dependency modules of this module are already put in
'vendor/mediatek/proprietary/external/ccci_mdinit_src/' folder.

HOW TO USE IT?
==============
The bin file is a system service, and it's started at system booting up while parsing init.cccimdinit.rc.